</a></ins>在未支付的法律费用和旧金山市<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/san-francisco-is-reportedly-investigating-twitter-over-possible-building-code-violations-113721801.html">调查潜在的建筑规范违规行为</a></ins>关于其主要总部。针对 Twitter 的其他诉讼参考了<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-faces-lawsuit-for-allegedly-getting-a-saudi-dissident-imprisoned-061457663.html">沙特持不同政见者入狱</a></ins>和<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-ftc-is-investigating-elon-musks-handling-of-twitter-blue-and-the-twitter-files-233539305.html">错误处理基于 FTC 的规章制度</a></ins>，等等。</p><p>推特解散了它的新闻部门和它的<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-dissolves-its-trust-and-safety-council-064143124.html">信托与安全委员会，</a></ins>所以没有人可以联系到评论。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/twitter-is-getting-evicted-from-its-colorado-office-over-unpaid-rent-185026284.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twitter-is-getting-evicted-from-its-colorado-office-over-unpaid-rent-185026284.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 951b7229-674a-4d56-84ad-24db6bdc76a3</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 14 Jun 2023 18:50:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686768627</ingested><modified> 2023-06-14T18:50:30+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="5075" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/f7abaee0-b2b2-11ed-b9fd-e485b9e94bee" width="7609"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="5075" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/f7abaee0-b2b2-11ed-b9fd-e485b9e94bee" width="7609"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Dado Ruvic / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A keyboard is placed in front of a displayed Twitter logo in this illustration taken February 21, 2023. REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Illustration]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[TECH-TWITTER/]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Saturn’s moon Enceladus could support species similar to Earth]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>土星的卫星土卫二含有磷。这一发现来自<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Nature Research;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c6c965be-a8ea-473d-89f4-9754f2675a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Nature+Research&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjNmM5NjViZS1hOGVhLTQ3M2QtODlmNC05NzU0ZjI2NzVhNjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmF0dXJlLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zNDE1ODYtMDIzLTA1OTg3LTkiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjkyNWU1MTQ1LWYyODItNGViOC1hZTk3LTNlYzYxOGQ2ZGI4MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAATp29xRoDZWV3YNEMQi27z1pgRp_YsEuxF8VCtS_inA4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41586-023-05987-9" class="rapid-with-clickid">最近分析的冰粒子，这些冰粒子</a>从天然卫星的海洋羽流中散发出来，由美国宇航局的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-11-24-nasas-cassini-probe-bids-farewell-to-saturn-with-epic-image.html">卡西尼号宇宙飞船</a>探测到。这一发现意味着土卫二拥有我们在地球上所知的所有生命化学组成部分。 “这是最后一个说法，‘是的，土卫二确实拥有典型地球生命生存所需的所有成分，而且正如我们所知，那里的海洋适合生命居住，”美国宇航局喷气推进的天体生物学家摩根凯布尔说。实验室， <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Wall Street Journal;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2f007401-3eaa-4237-b69b-54ccbe125502&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZBUZiVhughgsU0R3xZsiMmmiNUdbLCKgL4u1zK4codh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fsaturn-moon-enceladus-life-b9d53f97" class="rapid-with-clickid">告诉</a><em>华尔街日报</em>。</p><p>卡西尼号于 2017 年在土星大气层中<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-09-15-cassini-end-of-mission-rip.html">坠毁</a>，它通过土卫二在其南极不断喷发的间歇泉和土星的 E 环收集数据，其中还包含从月球逃逸的粒子。在冰冷的地壳下，土卫二有一个 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2015-09-15-enceladus-global-ocean.html">温暖的地下海洋</a>，深度超过 30 英里，包裹着整个月球。南极的喷发将冰质颗粒喷入太空，使像卡西尼号这样的研究飞船能够在不下水甚至不接触月球表面的情况下研究海洋的化学成分。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/dcc672e0-0adc-11ee-beff-d1a92db04dbc" style="height:1125px;width:2000px;" alt="NASA 图表展示了土星卫星土卫二的横截面。它显示了南极地区的冰壳、全球海洋、岩石核心和活跃的喷流。" data-uuid="5bb69e76-0616-35fd-97f2-6aa94a977c3c"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">美国宇航局</div></figure><p>之前任务的数据表明，月球拥有生命所需的所有基本组成部分——碳、氢、氮、氧和硫——除了磷。一组行星科学家在最初被研究人员忽视的大约 1,000 个样本中发现了 9 个含有磷酸盐（磷与氧原子结合）的颗粒。检测到的微量反映了磷的稀缺性。 “在六种生物必需元素中，磷是迄今为止宇宙中最稀有的元素，”该研究的第一作者弗兰克波斯特伯格说。</p><p>当然，土卫二包含生命需求并不一定意味着月球上就存在生命。 “下一步是弄清楚它是否确实有人居住，并且需要未来的任务来回答这个问题，”Cable 说。 “但这令人兴奋，因为它使土卫二成为进行此类搜索的更有吸引力的目的地。”当<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-06-27-nasa-dragonfly-mission-saturn-titan.html">蜻蜓任务</a>于 2027 年前往土星的卫星土卫六时，NASA 将有机会了解更多信息；另一个计划中的任务可能在 2050 年左右到达土卫二。此外， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/james-webb-telescope-finds-water-around-a-comet-in-the-main-asteroid-belt-203825983.html">詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜</a>可能有助于进一步阐明土卫二温暖的地下海洋的化学分解。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/saturns-moon-enceladus-could-support-species-similar-to-earth-182535342.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/saturns-moon-enceladus-could-support-species-similar-to-earth-182535342.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 925e5145-f282-4eb8-ae97-3ec618d6db80</guid><dc:creator>威尔尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 14 Jun 2023 18:25:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686766602</ingested><modified> 2023-06-14T18:16:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Industrials]]></category><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="3804" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/70aba9c0-8c3f-11ed-8f9f-20dc5abd6b78" width="5906"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3804" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/70aba9c0-8c3f-11ed-8f9f-20dc5abd6b78" width="5906"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[All About Space Magazine via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Illustration of vapour plumes erupting from the surface of Enceladus, Saturns sixth largest moon, created on July 26, 2018. (Illustration by Tobias Roetsch/Future Publishing via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Enceladus (Moon Of Saturn) Illustration]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CD